(ï CRITICAL: aws_db_instance.primary will be destroyed and recreated. This causes) Tj
T* (production database downtime and risks data loss if the final snapshot is not taken or) Tj
T* (restored correctly.) Tj
T* (Fix: resource "aws_db_instance" "primary" {) Tj
T* (ï CRITICAL: aws_db_instance.replica will be permanently destroyed. This eliminates read) Tj
T* (scaling capacity and the replica's data will be lost.) Tj
T* (Fix: resource "aws_db_instance" "replica" {) Tj
T* (ï HIGH RISK: aws_security_group.bastion exposes SSH \(port 22\) and RDP \(port 3389\) to the) Tj
T* (entire internet \(0.0.0.0/0\), making the bastion host a high-value attack target.) Tj
T* (Fix: resource "aws_security_group" "bastion" {) Tj
T* (ï HIGH RISK: aws_ebs_volume.data has encrypted = false. Unencrypted EBS volumes storing) Tj
T* (production data violate most compliance frameworks and expose data at rest.) Tj
T* (Fix: resource "aws_ebs_volume" "data" {) Tj
T* (ï HIGH RISK: aws_db_instance.primary and aws_db_instance.replica both have) Tj
T* (storage_encrypted = false. Production RDS instances should always use encryption at rest.) Tj
T* (Fix: resource "aws_db_instance" "primary" {) Tj
T* (ï MEDIUM RISK: aws_iam_user.deploy is granted AmazonS3FullAccess and) Tj
T* (AmazonEC2FullAccess via IAM user policy attachments. Using long-lived IAM user) Tj
T* (credentials with broad permissions violates least-privilege principles; prefer IAM roles with) Tj
T* (scoped policies.) Tj
T* (Fix: resource "aws_iam_role" "deploy" {) Tj
T* (ï MEDIUM RISK: aws_cloudtrail.main has is_multi_region_trail = false. A single-region trail) Tj
T* (will miss API activity in other AWS regions, creating audit blind spots.) Tj
T* (Fix: resource "aws_cloudtrail" "main" {) Tj
T* (ï MEDIUM RISK: aws_lambda_function.processor uses runtime python3.8, which is) Tj
T* (approaching end-of-life. Upgrade to python3.11 or python3.12 to receive security patches.) Tj
T* (Fix: resource "aws_lambda_function" "processor" {) Tj
T* (ï MEDIUM RISK: aws_eks_cluster.main uses Kubernetes version 1.24, which is end-of-life) Tj
T* (and no longer receives security patches from AWS. Upgrade to a supported version \(1.29+\).) Tj
T* (Fix: resource "aws_eks_cluster" "main" {) Tj
T* (ï MEDIUM RISK: module.eks has no version constraint pinned. Unpinned modules can) Tj
T* (silently pull in breaking changes on the next terraform init, leading to unintended) Tj
T* (infrastructure mutations.) Tj
